task.summary: Default task
Added id autoincr for enemies, finished basic visitor structure in entity.
Documented entity package.
Added Event and Skill skeletons.
Starting instruction set for events.
Added untested bodies to EventQueue and Event classes.
Completed Event class, Standardized loading methods via deletion of static blocks.
Updated UML class diagram, Created skeleton of Enemy composition class
Removed Occupant class.
Added proper Opcode enum
Grid cleanup
Methods filled for EnemyRoster, general readability improvements.
Revised grid/roster methods to accompany dual maps.
Revised grid/roster methods to accompany dual maps.
Refactored item classes.
Item classes functional.
Small fix to EventQueue timing, time now entered on a consistent basis.
Implemented enum for common display states
Various renaming, fixes
Changed TriConsumer to QuadConsumer
Added new system to work with groups of instructions on keypress, incredibly rough
Implemented key binding restriction/expansion in Display
Created Executable superclass to condense (Macro)Event data.
Updated Get ('g') keybind to work with new system.
Reworked asm, added methods to Grid/Catalog to support item removal between the amounts of 1 and all.
Cleaned up GUI(Focus&Sidebar)
Fixed bug with Items keeping their stats on use.
Fixed collision detection on untraversible tiles.
Revised focusing on grid, fixed issue where descriptions would not show initially on command press.
Events now return a string, which is forwarded to the Message Manager. Incredibly buggy, but the framework is made up.
Optimized Response String formatting.
Various Cleanup, Added Event[] as return type for AI
Added comments to most methods.
Fixed key input issues throwing exceptions in improper conditions (typing 'g' when there are no items on the tile, e.g.)
Added functionality for backing out of prompts, as well as escaping them altogether.
Grid focus now snaps to player when backing into a Tile Prompt or exiting a series of prompts.
Removed Header from the display.
Added proper state swapping for GUIFooter.
Replaced Display States with enums.
Added DialogueParser.
Added proper (and crude) dialogue display and nav.
Split Display into a view (Display, GUIComponent conglomerate) and a model (PromptManager, Adjusts Display).
Added dialogue start functionality on event call.
Added javadoc, revised copy constructor for Combatant subclasses.
Standardized Instruction inputs to a 7-variable standard.
Renamed files for clarity.
Consolidated Opcode into Event wildcard.
Removed Builder pattern in lieu of built-in fluency in Event.
Added Flag skeletons.
Revised Combatant Parser, as well as Flag parsing.
